@startuml
title Response and Recovery Workflow

' Palette
' #211951 (deep navy)
' #836FFF (violet)
' #15F5BA (mint)
' #F0F3FF (soft white)

skinparam backgroundColor #F0F3FF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontColor #211951
skinparam ArrowColor #211951
skinparam ArrowThickness 1

skinparam activityStartColor #15F5BA
skinparam activityEndColor #15F5BA
skinparam activityBarColor #211951
skinparam activityDiamondBackgroundColor #836FFF
skinparam activityDiamondBorderColor #211951
skinparam activityDiamondFontColor #F0F3FF
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #F0F3FF
skinparam activityBorderColor #211951
skinparam activityFontColor #211951

start
:Monitoring detects error spikes\nor support receives complaints;
:Incident manager is activated;

if (Is customer impact confirmed?) then (Yes)
  :Classify severity\n(critical/high/medium);
else (No)
  :Continue observation and diagnostics;
  stop
endif

if (Is this a provider-wide issue?) then (Yes)
  :Switch to continuity mode and\nfocus on customer-safe fallback;
else (No)
  :Apply local fix and monitor recovery;
endif

fork
  :Traffic actions:\nRoute users to healthy region;
fork again
  :Application actions:\nEnable degraded mode\n(guest browsing/guest checkout where allowed);
fork again
  :Dependency actions:\nRetry/queue payment requests\nand apply login fallback options;
fork again
  :Communication actions:\nPublish status page update\nand internal incident update;
end fork

if (Are checkout and login stable?) then (Yes)
  :Maintain heightened monitoring;
  :Announce service stabilization;
else (No)
  :Escalate to secondary recovery plan\nand continue mitigations;
endif

:Run post-incident review;
:Track corrective actions and\nschedule continuity test;
stop

legend right
Visual key
Start/End (mint): Workflow begins and ends
Decision (violet): Yes/No choice point
Action (soft white): Concrete team step
Arrows (navy): Order of operations
---
Plain-English guide:
1) Confirm customer impact.
2) Decide if issue is local or provider-wide.
3) In parallel, handle routing, app fallback,
   dependency issues, and communication.
4) Stay in recovery mode until login and checkout stabilize.
5) Run post-incident review and improvement actions.
endlegend

@enduml